 <title>Reprieve for Ray Sandford</title>
 <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/disabilitynation/~3/okUNBdUApKk/reprieve-ray-sandford</link>
 <description>&lt;span class="inline inline-right"&gt;&lt;img src="/files/images/Sandford.img_assist_custom.jpg" alt="Photo of Ray Sandford. Photo by Daryl Trones of City Pages." title="Photo of Ray Sandford. Photo by Daryl Trones of City Pages."  class="image image-img_assist_custom" width="250" height="250" /&gt;&lt;span class="caption" style="width: 248px;"&gt;Photo of Ray Sandford. Photo by Daryl Trones of City Pages.&lt;/span&gt;&lt;/span&gt;&lt;p&gt;DisabilityNation has continued to follow the story of Ray Sandford for the past few months. Back in April you'll recall that &lt;a href="http://www.disabilitynation.net/blog/ray-sandford-declares-guarded-victory-mindfreedom-ray-campaign"&gt;Ray's psychiatrist quit&lt;/a&gt; giving hope that the forced shock treatments he was receiving would soon end. Last week an article appeared in City Pages that did an excellent job of describing what Ray has been subjected to because of these treatments. City Pages is the main weekly newspaper distributed throughout Â 
Minneapolis/St. Paul, Minnesota.
 
