 <title>Why I Really Didn't Like "How's Your News?"</title>
 <link>http://feedproxy.google.com/~r/disabilitynation/~3/5CQBT6sih3A/why-i-really-didnt-hows-your-news</link>
 <description>&lt;p&gt; I really hoped I would dig &lt;a href="http://www.howsyournews.com"&gt;How's Your News?&lt;/a&gt;, even if liking the &lt;a href="http://www.mtv.com"&gt;MTV&lt;/a&gt; chatfest puts me on the same side as curmudgeonly media critic Tom Shales, who has failed to spot a trend or have an original thought since Poppy and Bar went back to Kennebunkport.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;object width="425" height="344"&gt;&lt;param name="movie" value="http://www.youtube.com/v/fgW7eVI5iYA&amp;hl=en&amp;fs=1"&gt;&lt;/param&gt;&lt;param name="allowFullScreen" value="true"&gt;&lt;/param&gt;&lt;param name="allowscriptaccess" value="always"&gt;&lt;/param&gt;&lt;embed src="http://www.youtube.com/v/fgW7eVI5iYA&amp;hl=en&amp;fs=1" type="application/x-shockwave-flash" allowscriptaccess="always" allowfullscreen="true" width="425" height="344"&gt;&lt;/embed&gt;&lt;/object&gt;

&lt;p&gt; I didn't have to worry about that, since I found every moment of &lt;i&gt; News&lt;/i&gt; more painful than the one before, despite my generally positive feelings about people with disabilities doing man-on-the-street interviews.&lt;/p&gt;&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href="http://www.disabilitynation.net/blog/why-i-really-didnt-hows-your-news"&gt;read more&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;&lt;div class="feedflare"&gt;
